I have created a window in the editor and I needed to change the order of items, when layout is enabled. I looked into the source code and I found two places where it is forbidden to deliberately.

In engine:

```
void UIElement::SortChildren()
{
    if (sortChildren_ && sortOrderDirty_)
    {
        // Only sort when there is no layout
        /// \todo Order is not stable when children have same priorities
        if (layoutMode_ == LM_FREE)
            Sort(children_.Begin(), children_.End(), CompareUIElements);
        sortOrderDirty_ = false;
    }
}
```

In editor:

```
        // Do not allow UI subsystem to reorder children while editing the element in the editor
        element.sortChildren = false;
```

I would like to remove these restrictions, but I'm afraid disrupt engine. What is their purpose?
